# Project Standards

## Formatting

- **indentSize**: 2
- **useTabs**: true
- **trimTrailingWhitespace**: true
- **insertFinalNewline**: true
- **trailingComma**: "all"
- **semi**: true (semicolons required)
- **singleQuote**: true (single quotes only)
- **maxLineLength**: 100 characters

## Analysis

- **enforceTypeScript**: true
- **enforceESLint**: true
- **enforcePrettier**: true

## Search Exclude Patterns

- node_modules/**, dist/**, client/assets/video/**
- **/*.png, **/*.jpg, **/*.jpeg, **/*.gif, **/*.svg, **/*.ico, **/*.webp
- **/*.mp4, **/*.mp3, **/*.wav, **/*.ogg, **/*.flac
- **/.DS_Store, **/*.log, records.json, report.html

## Naming Conventions

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| **Function** | ^[a-z][a-zA-Z0-9]*$ | appleTree |
| **CSS Class** | ^[a-z][a-z0-9-]*$ | apple-tree |
| **Class Name** | ^[A-Z][a-zA-Z0-9]*$ | AppleTree |
| **Constant** | ^[A-Z][A-Z0-9_]*$ | APPLE_TREE |

## Code Reuse

**Rule**: Maximum reuse of utilities code.

**Requirements**:
- Always check existing utilities before implementing new functionality
- Import and reuse utility functions from `client/js/core/` and `helpers/` directories
- Never duplicate utility functionality - use existing utilities instead
- If similar functionality exists, extend or refactor existing utilities rather than creating duplicates
- Before writing new helper functions, search for existing utilities that can be reused or extended

**Utility Locations**:
- `client/js/core/` - Core client-side utilities (format, validate, query, log, load, etc.)
- `helpers/` - Server-side and shared utilities (geo, fuse, mappers, etc.)

**Checklist**:
- Search existing utilities before implementing new functionality
- Import from appropriate utility modules
- Extend existing utilities if needed rather than duplicating
- Document any new utility functions added
